03/05/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- The signatories to the Adriatic Charter -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia -- marked the second anniversary of its signing with a conference on Monday (2 May). 
The focus was on the progress made so far towards NATO integration. 
US representative Kathleen Stephens said Washington welcomes and supports the continuing co-operation among the three countries, adding that the charter plays an important role in maintaining regional stability. 
Conference attendees included NATO Assistant Secretary General Guenter Alenburg and representatives of Bosnia and Herzegovina and Serbia-Montenegro, future signatories to the charter. 
(Albanian Daily News - 03/05/05; HINA, ATA - 02/05/05)
